2009/12/4 Ken <kstanley@...>
>
> SharpNEAT is certainly more recently updated and also more optimized (as Colin Green can tell you) but JNEAT should generally
> still work. So I think it's still just a matter of what is most important to you.

I'd just add that if you do look at SharpNEAT then be aware that the
1.04 version on sourcefiorge dates back to 2006. The latest
development code is a rewrite/refactoring and might be worth look at
perhaps just to see if the class framework fits your needs better.
Current status and zip of the source is available here:

http://sites.google.com/site/sharpneat/dev-releases-status

If you have Visual studio 2005 or above then it will compile and run
without any hassle. Although from what David was sayign in another
recent email it seems that loading the project in MonoDevelop on Linux
is pretty straightforward also.

Colin
